UGHELLI – The Delta State Commissioner for Water Resources Development, Rt. Hon. Evelyn Omavowan Oboro Esq., has joined well-wishers in rejoicing with the Delta State Secretary of the Peoples’ Democratic Party,  Hon Engr. Dan Ossai on the occasion of his birthday anniversary, describing him as a goal-getter. Oboro in a congratulatory message signed by her Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Hon. Sunday Apah, described Hon. Ossai as a man of impeccable character that has propelled the activities of the party in the state to an enviable height. According to her, the ‘birthday man’ is a vibrant scribe of the party, whose activities has sold the party to the downtrodden citizens in the state. And his relationship with the capacity state chairman of the party and other members of the state executive of the party has started yielding good results. Oboro Celebrates Onoyake, Uvwie Council Boss On His Birthday… Birthday: Northern Governors Celebrate Kebbi, Nasarawa Governors “I, on behalf of my family, friends and political associates, congratulate you on your birthday. May the years ahead offer you great moments of accomplishment and desired victories, even as you continue to stand firm in service of God and man,” she added